Package org.odpi.openmetadata.accessservices.subjectarea.properties.objects.nodesummary

Class NodeSummary

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.odpi.openmetadata.accessservices.subjectarea.properties.objects.nodesummary.NodeSummary
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AssetSummary, CanonicalGlossarySummary, CanonicalTaxonomySummary, CategorySummary, GlossarySummary, TaxonomySummary, TermSummary
    public class NodeSummary
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A SummaryNode represents a node in the subject area omas that has a type NodeType, relationship type, name and icon. A Summary Node is used when a Node needs to hold a reference to another node. It contains only fields useful for identification.
